text: Feels bad when Artifact, Richard Garfield’s new game that’s been out <1 year already has approaching double the viewers as MTG
Especially on a pro tour weekend.
What is it?

Online card game.
You have to manage three independent board states by allocating the cards in your hand to each one. Your goal is to break towers controlled by your opponent. First to break two is the winner.

I haven’t played it (I didn’t even realize it was out yet), but it looks really interesting.
Cool
Some mtg pros were saying it’s really well done and interesting.
Apparently today is a preview tournament. The game releases Nov. 28.

There’s a couple folks who skipped the PT to do that instead. Mainly European players

I watched a video on it a while back.
Garfield wanted to have a lot of decisions to make akin to Magic, but he thought Magic’s priority system didn’t translate to online as well. He wanted to make a very fluid system from what I remember.
I’m interested in trying it out.

I’ll try to find the video I watched.
